# 🔐 Nginx + SSL Setup on CentOS

A simple hands-on exercise to install and configure Nginx with a self-signed SSL certificate on a CentOS Stream server.

## 🛠️ Steps Covered

1. Install Nginx using `yum`
2. Move existing SSL cert and key to `/etc/nginx/ssl/`
3. Configure Nginx to serve HTTPS
4. Add `index.html` with "Welcome!" message
5. Test the setup using `curl -Ik https://<server-ip>`

## 🗂️ Files Included

- `nginx.conf` — Sample HTTPS server block
- `index.html` — Basic web page content
- `setup.sh` *(optional)* — Script to automate steps

## 🚀 Commands Used

```bash
sudo yum install nginx
sudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/ssl
sudo mv /tmp/nautilus.crt /etc/nginx/ssl/
sudo mv /tmp/nautilus.key /etc/nginx/ssl/
sudo vi /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
echo "Welcome!" | sudo tee /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo curl -Ik https://<server-ip>
